bib_record.title: Statistical and direct aspects of 64Zn(gamma,n) and (gamma,np) decay channels in the giant dipole resonance and quasideuteron energy regions.

free_txt: reaction cross sections using virtual photon
The investigation of statistical and direct aspects
related to the (g,n) and (g,np) decay channels of
64Zn in the giant dipole resonance (GDR) and
quasideuteron (QD) energy regions was performed by a
trial function fitting to the respective (e,n) and
residual activity. Absolute cross section for the
reaction 64Zn(g,n) from threshold to 60 MeV was
obtained for the first time. Statistical and direct
contributions to the (g,np) process, later being
remarkably well described by the QD model were
separated in the interval 40 - 60 MeV. A possible
direct contribution for the (g,n) decay in GDR was
also addressed. The total photoabsorption cross
section of 64Zn was reevaluated up to 21 MeV.
